<subSubSection id="C322B4E76674FFC4FF0B07886BE29952" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6674FFC4FF0B07886C5398EA" blockId="18.[151,1437,152,431]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FF0B0788696F98A2" bold="true" box="[151,305,152,179]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">Distribution.</emphasis>
Distributed throughout the northern GOM, from southern Florida to the Texas/ 
<collectingCountry id="F32FA7FC6674FFC4FB3007896D5F98A2" box="[1196,1281,153,179]" name="Mexico" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">Mexico</collectingCountry>
border, in estuaries and nearshore waters. This species is commonly reported from the shoreline out to approximately 
<quantity id="4CC04A896674FFC4FABB07AD6D0F98C6" box="[1319,1361,189,215]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" unit="m" value="9.0">9 m</quantity>
depth, although NMFS SEFSC trawl surveys have documented them as deep as 
<specimenCount id="9D3E2CE56674FFC4FC5107F16C5398EA" box="[973,1037,225,251]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" type="generic">
<quantity id="4CC04A896674FFC4FC5107F16C5798EA" box="[973,1033,225,251]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" unit="m" value="40.0">40 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6674FFC4FF5B06146BE29952" blockId="18.[151,1437,152,431]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FF5B0614698A990E" bold="true" box="[199,468,260,287]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">First Record in GOM.</emphasis>
This species was first reported from the northern GOM by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FBE706156D6D990E" author="Henshall, J. A." box="[1147,1331,261,287]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" pagination="209 - 221" refId="ref17889" refString="Henshall, J. A. (1894) Notes on fishes collected in Florida. Bulletin of the United States Fish Commission, 14, 209 - 221." type="journal article" year="1894">Henshall (1894)</bibRefCitation>
, who describes capturing an individual near the entrance to Tampa Bay in 1892.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322B4E76674FFC4FF5B065D6A3499BE" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6674FFC4FF5B065D6BA2999A" blockId="18.[151,1437,152,431]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FF5B065D69659976" bold="true" box="[199,315,333,359]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6674FFC4FE26065E6AB99976" authority="Rafinesque, 1818" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1818" box="[442,743,333,359]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FE26065E6A409976" box="[442,542,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">Hypanus</emphasis>
Rafinesque, 1818
</taxonomicName>
was previously considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C389CEF6674FFC4FA9D065E6D3D9976" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1810" box="[1281,1379,334,359]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FA9D065E6D3D9976" box="[1281,1379,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">Dasyatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until resurrected by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA99A9D6674FFC4FEA2066169A1999D" author="Last, P. &amp; White, W. T. &amp; de Carvalho, M. R. &amp; Seret, B. &amp; Stehmann, M. F. W. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P." box="[318,511,369,396]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299" refId="ref18676" refString="Last, P., White, W. T., de Carvalho, M. R., Seret, B., Stehmann, M. F. W. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P. (Eds.), (2016) Rays of the World. CSIRO publishing. Melbourne, 790 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / 9780643109148" type="book" year="2016">
Last 
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FEE9066269F3999A" box="[373,429,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
based predominantly on molecular evidence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B87E76C6674FFC4FF5B06846A3499BE" blockId="18.[151,1437,152,431]" box="[199,618,404,431]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B94C3B7E6674FFC4FF5B0684699E99BE" bold="true" box="[199,448,404,431]" pageId="18" pageNumber="299">Conservation Status.</emphasis>
